snippet: Emmanuel Emenike scored twice as the African champion Nigeria came from behind to win, 2-1, at Ethiopia in the first leg of the African qualifying playoffs for the 2014 World Cup.
abstract: Nigeria defeats Ethiopia, 2-1, in first leg of the African qualifying playoffs for the 2014 World Cup; other soccer news noted.
lead_paragraph: Emmanuel Emenike scored twice as the African champion Nigeria came from behind to win, 2-1, at Ethiopia in the first leg of the African qualifying playoffs for the 2014 World Cup.
